# React + Vite

This template provides a minimal setup to get React working in Vite with HMR and some ESLint rules.

Currently, two official plugins are available:

- [@vitejs/plugin-react](https://github.com/vitejs/vite-plugin-react/blob/main/packages/plugin-react) uses [Babel](https://babeljs.io/) (or [oxc](https://oxc.rs) when used in [rolldown-vite](https://vite.dev/guide/rolldown)) for Fast Refresh
- [@vitejs/plugin-react-swc](https://github.com/vitejs/vite-plugin-react/blob/main/packages/plugin-react-swc) uses [SWC](https://swc.rs/) for Fast Refresh

## React Compiler

The React Compiler is not enabled on this template because of its impact on dev & build performances. To add it, see [this documentation](https://react.dev/learn/react-compiler/installation).

## Expanding the ESLint configuration

If you are developing a production application, we recommend using TypeScript with type-aware lint rules enabled. Check out the [TS template](https://github.com/vitejs/vite/tree/main/packages/create-vite/template-react-ts) for information on how to integrate TypeScript and [`typescript-eslint`](https://typescript-eslint.io) in your project.
🛒 POS System
A full-featured Point of Sale system built with React + Node.js.
📋 Build Roadmap
⚙️ Phase 1 — Project Setup & Planning
[ ] Choose Your Tech Stack — React (frontend), Node.js (backend), MySQL (database)
[ ] Set Up GitHub Repository — Initialize repo, set main branch, save PAT token
[ ] Initialize Your Project — Set up Vite + React, folder structure, install dependencies
[ ] Design the Database Schema — Plan tables: Products, Categories, Sales, SaleItems, Users
[ ] Set Up the Backend Server — Node.js + Express, connect to database, test /api/health endpoint
🔐 Phase 2 — Authentication System
[ ] Build Login Page UI — Clean login form with username/password and validation
[ ] Set Up User Roles — Admin (full access) and Cashier (sale screen only)
[ ] Implement JWT Authentication — Generate tokens on login, protect all API routes
[ ] Build Role-Based Route Protection — PrivateRoute component, redirect unauthorized users
📦 Phase 3 — Product & Inventory Management
[ ] Build Product List Page — Table/grid with search bar and category filter
[ ] Add Product Form — Fields: Name, Price, Category, Stock, Barcode, Image
[ ] Edit & Delete Products — Pre-fill form on edit, confirmation dialog on delete
[ ] Stock/Inventory Tracking — Auto-deduct stock on sale, low stock warnings
[ ] Category Management — Add, rename, delete categories from admin panel
🛒 Phase 4 — Point of Sale Screen (Core Feature)
[ ] Build the POS Layout — Split screen: product grid (left) + cart/order (right)
[ ] Product Search & Selection — Search by name or barcode, click to add to cart
[ ] Cart / Order Management — Quantities with +/- buttons, line totals, grand total
[ ] Payment Processing — Cash payment modal, calculate change, record sale in DB
[ ] Receipt Generation — Itemized receipt with print button
[ ] Barcode Scanner Support — Camera or USB barcode scanner integration
📊 Phase 5 — Reports & Analytics
[ ] Daily Sales Report — Total transactions, revenue, most sold products
[ ] Sales History Table — All past transactions with date range filter
[ ] Revenue Chart — Line/bar chart of daily/weekly/monthly revenue
[ ] Top Selling Products — Ranked list of best sellers within a date range
[ ] Export Reports — Download sales data as CSV or PDF
✨ Phase 6 — Settings & Final Polish
[ ] Store Settings Page — Store name, logo, currency, tax rate, receipt footer
[ ] User Management — Add/deactivate cashier accounts, view cashier activity
[ ] Responsive Design — Optimized for tablet and desktop touchscreens
[ ] Error Handling & Validation — Out-of-stock guards, network errors, user-friendly messages
[ ] Deploy the Application — Backend on Railway/Render, Frontend on Vercel, DB on PlanetScale
